╭─ Assistant [MainThread@2734469] ──────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ The patch modifies ConstraintElimination to avoid introducing poison when     │
│ simplifying disjoint OR operations.                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Problem:                                                                      │
│ Simplifying “or disjoint” by replacing an operand with a constant based on    │
│ implications from the other operand can violate the disjointness promise.     │
│ Specifically, replacing an operand with true may cause both operands to be    │
│ true simultaneously, making the result poison, while the original was not.    │
│ This is demonstrated by the reproducer and Alive2 counterexample.             │
│                                                                               │
│ Fix:                                                                          │
│ In checkOrAndOpImpliedByOther(), before performing the replacement, if the    │
│ join is an OR and has the disjoint flag set and the implied condition is      │
│ true, the transformation is skipped. This preserves correctness by not making │
│ the instruction more poisonous.                                               │
│                                                                               │
│ Files changed:                                                                │
│ - llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                        │
│                                                                               │
│ Key change:                                                                   │
│ - Add a guard to bail out when attempting to replace an operand with true on  │
│ a disjoint OR:                                                                │
│                                                                               │
│   if (IsOr) {                                                                 │
│     if (auto *PDI = dyn_cast<PossiblyDisjointInst>(JoinOp)) {                 │
│       if (PDI->isDisjoint() && *ImpliedCondition)                             │
│         return false;                                                         │
│     }                                                                         │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Note:                                                                         │
│ - This is a targeted fix for the correctness issue with disjoint OR           │
│ simplification.                                                               │
│ - Some existing tests expect prior (unsafe) transformations and will fail due │
│ to this correctness-preserving change.                                        │
